Data.event_text: - A suicide bomber identified as Nur Rohman, 30, attacked a police headquarters in Surakarta, Indonesia after being denied entry to the building. The blast, which was described as a "low explosive blast", injured an officer's face. Nur Rohman, the perpetrator, was the only casualty. Nur Rohman initially tried to detonate his explosives while the police conducting a morning ceremony. The attack occurred just one day before Indonesia celebrates Eid-Al-Fitr. President Joko Widodo cut short his visit in Padang, and ordered police to tighten security in Indonesia. Minister of Tourism stated that Indonesians should not be scared due to the incident. Police later announced that Nur Rohman was linked with the Jakarta attacks earlier in January, and stated that this incident might be ISIL inspired.

links.text: -"Helikopter TNI AD jatuh di Yogyakarta, tiga meninggal". BBC. 8 July 2016. Retrieved 9 July 2016.-
-"Mabes TNI AD Bantah Helikopter Jatuh saat Patroli Jelang Kunjungan Presiden". Kompas. Retrieved 9 July 2016.-
-"Ini Sosok Perempuan Korban Heli Jatuh di Yogyakarta". Liputan6. 8 July 2016. Retrieved 9 July 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Indonesian government confirmed that 3 Indonesians were abducted and taken hostage by Philippines' terrorist group Abu Sayyaf, making the total number of Indonesians taken hostage by Abu Sayyaf to 10.

links.text: -"Panglima TNI: 3 WNI Disandera Kelompok Abu Sayyaf". Kompas. Retrieved 11 July 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Mount Barujari erupted, prompting the closure of Lombok International Airport in Lombok.

links.text: -"Anak Gunung Rinjani Meletus, Bandara Lombok Tutup Sementara : Okezone News". August 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Anniesa Hasibuan makes history as the first Indonesian designer in the New York Fashion Week and the first in the history of the event that features "a collection of hijabs in every look".

links.text: -"History made in New York as one designer shows the first-ever collection to feature hijabs in every look". CNN.-
-"Saat hijab karya Anniesa Hasibuan tampil memukau di New York Fashion Week". 17 September 2016.-
-"Muslim fashion designer makes history with hijab collection at New York Fashion Week". Independent. Archived from the original on 2022-05-01.-
-"Muslim fashion designer makes history with hijab collection at New York Fashion Week". Independent. Archived from the original on 2022-05-01.-

Data.event_text: - Massive explosion occurred on the suburb of Makassar, South Sulawesi. The explosion was caused due to gas leak. Damages in the neighborhood were massive, with cars flipped and buildings destroyed.

links.text: -"Ini Penampakan Tempat Kejadian Pasca-Ledakan di Makassar : Okezone News". 12 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: - An explosion occurred on board the Gili Cat 2 ship in Bali while en route to Gili Trawangan, a popular island resort. 2 people were killed and 20 people were injured in the incident. Police suspected that the fuel tank located on the rear of the boat contacted a faulty wire on the boat, causing a short circuit that led to the explosion.

links.text: -"Ledakan kapal di Bali tewaskan dua turis asing". 16 September 2016.-
-"Wisatawan Asing Korban Ledakan Kapal di Padangbai Dibawa ke Denpasar".-
-"Korban Ledakan Kapal Dibawa ke Denpasar". 15 September 2016.-
-"Dua WNA yang Meninggal dalam Ledakan Kapal di Bali Segera Diautopsi".-

Data.event_text: - A grenade was thrown into a Local Representative's car and exploded in Bener Meriah, Aceh Province. 2 people were killed instantly, including a 5-year-old boy. The third was pronounced dead at hospital. A manhunt was ordered immediately after the blast.

links.text: -"BREAKING NEWS: Granat Meledak Dalam Mobil Anggota DPRK Bener Meriah, Seorang Bocah Tewas".-
-"1 Lagi Korban Granat Bener Meriah Meninggal Dunia". 23 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: Three Indonesians that had previously taken hostages by Philippines terrorist group Abu Sayyaf were released.

links.text: -"Ditebus 30 Juta Peso, 3 Sandera WNI Dibebaskan Abu Sayyaf -News » Harian Jogja". Archived from the original on 2016-11-07. Retrieved 2016-11-06.-
-"Ditebus 30 Juta Peso, 3 Sandera WNI Dibebaskan Abu Sayyaf -News » Harian Jogja". Archived from the original on 2016-11-07. Retrieved 2016-11-06.-

Data.event_text: Garut flash flood - A massive, 'tsunami-like' flash flood struck the city of Garut during the early hours of . The Cimanuk River suddenly overflow, and a large, massive wall of water suddenly swept the residential area around the river. At least 30 people were killed when the flood struck the city. Most of them were killed while in their sleep. 22 people were missing. Preliminary report suggests that 100 houses went missing during the disaster and 300 houses were either damaged or destroyed

links.text: -"Korban Tewas Banjir Bandang Garut Tambah Jadi 6 Orang, 16 Orang Lagi Hilang".-
-"Canda yang Jadi Kenyataan di Balik Banjir Bandang Garut : Okezone News". 24 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: Conflict arose between Google and the Indonesian Government as Google accused by the Indonesian Government for tax evasion.

links.text: -"Pajak Saja Tembus Triliunan Rupiah, Google Dapat Duit Dari Mana? Halaman all". 22 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: Another Indonesian identified as Herman has been released by Abu Sayyaf in the Philippines.

links.text: -"Militer Filipina Sebut WNI Bernama Herman Dibebaskan Abu Sayyaf".-

Data.event_text: - A pedestrian bridge in Jakarta collapsed during a massive storm. 3 people were killed in the incident. Several people blamed the weather condition for the cause of the collapse, while several others stated that advertising billboards on the bridge might have caused an overloading, causing the collapse.

links.text: -"Angin Berembus Kencang Saat JPO Pasar Minggu Roboh". 25 September 2016.-
-"Ini Penyebab Robohnya JPO di Pasar Minggu". 25 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Rioters burned the second floor of Gowa's Local Representative Building in Gowa, South Sulawesi. The arson started after a fight broke out during the protest.

links.text: -"Demo di Gowa Rusuh, Kantor DPRD Terbakar". 26 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A video of a young Indonesian diplomat Nara Masista Rakhmatia complaining about the statements of Papuan human rights violations made by Oceanian leaders from Solomon Islands, Vanuatu, Nauru, Marshall Islands, Tuvalu, and Tonga went viral in Indonesia. During the United Nations General Assembly, the six nations that complained about human rights condition in Papua were mocked and accused by the Indonesian Government for "falsely report and accusing Indonesians for Papuans human rights violations.

links.text: -"Diserang soal Papua di PBB, Diplomat Muda Indonesia Balas Para Pemimpin Negara Pasifik". 28 September 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Three Indonesians, who had been held hostage by Abu Sayyaf, were released in Sulu.

links.text: -"Lagi, Tiga WNI Dibebaskan Kelompok Abu Sayyaf". Kompas.-

Data.event_text: -A woman, identified as Mutmainah, was arrested by the police after mutilating her own children in Cengkareng. News of the incident was widely shared on social media.

links.text: -"Fokus: Kekejian Ibu Mutilasi Anak".-

Data.event_text: - A boat carrying 25 people sank in Bengawan Solo River. At least 7 people went missing, most of them were teenagers.

links.text: -"Tujuh santri yang tenggelam di Bengawan Solo belum ditemukan". 8 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: - All 7 missing people from Bengawan Solo boat accident were found, none survived.

links.text: -"7 Jenazah Santri Korban Perahu Tenggelam Ditemukan". 9 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A bomb exploded inside Golkar politician Marthinus Werimon's house in Kotaraja, Jayapura. No one was killed or injured in the incident, with only minimal damages were reported.
- At least 172 houses were destroyed and a further 265 houses were damaged after a tornado struck the city of Pangandaran, West Java. One person was killed indirectly.

links.text: -Aminuddin, Choirul (October 12, 2016). "Pangandaran Dilanda Angin Puting Beliung, 275 Rumah Rusak". Tempo.-

Data.event_text: - Following an outcry by campaigners and the Indonesian people, a new law on paedophiles was approved by the government. Paedophiles would face chemical castration and possibly execution under the new laws. The courts can also order the police to plant a microchip instead of a chemical castration to surveillance the paedophiles' movement.

links.text: -"Paedophiles to face chemical castration and possibly execution under Indonesia's brutal new laws". The Independent. Archived from the original on 2022-05-01.-
-"Paedophiles to face chemical castration and possibly execution under Indonesia's brutal new laws". The Independent. Archived from the original on 2022-05-01.-

Data.event_text: - After a long week of nationality issues, Archanda Tahar was inaugurated by President Joko Widodo as the Vice Minister of Energy and Human Resources, with Ignasius Jonan, the former Minister of Transportation, as the Minister of Energy and Human Resources.

links.text: -"Ignasius Jonan dan Arcandra Tahar diangkat jadi Menteri dan Wakil Menteri ESDM". 14 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A speedboat carrying more than 40 people caught fire shortly after departing Jailolo Harbour in West Halmahera. At least 41 people were injured and 4 people were killed in the incident. Police stated that the fire started when one of the engines failed. The fire then contacted gasoline and ignited a massive fire.

links.text: -IPTEK, Dody Hidayat-Reporter (October 15, 2016). "Kapal Cepat Jailolo-Ternate Terbakar, 4 Orang Tewas". Tempo.-
-"Kapal Cepat Terbakar di Halmahera, 4 Penumpang Tewas". 15 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A suspension bridge, named by the local as the Yellow Bridge in Klungkung, Bali, collapsed. At least 8 people were killed in the incident, 34 others were injured. Eyewitnesses stated that the slings that were holding the weight of the bridge suddenly snapped. This structural failure could have been caused by overloading, as witnesses stated that there were many people and motorcycles seconds before the collapse.

links.text: -"Jembatan di Bali ambruk, delapan dilaporkan tewas". 16 October 2016.-
-"Semua korban jembatan ambruk di Bali ditemukan, pencarian dihentikan". 17 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: Indonesia ratified the Paris Agreement.

links.text: -"Ratifikasi kesepakatan Paris, 'komitmen semua pihak dibutuhkan'". 19 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: An ISIS supporter, identified as Sultan Azianzah from South Tangerang, attacked three police officers in Tangerang police department with a knife. Sultan was shot by police and later pronounced dead at hospital. Two pipe bombs were recovered in the area near the attack site.

links.text: -setiawan, Kodrat (October 20, 2016). "3 Polisi di Tangerang Korban Serangan Dirujuk ke RS Siloam". Tempo.-

Data.event_text: - A massive explosion occurred on a Pizza Hut Delivery building in Bekasi. The blast were so massive that a supermarket nearby were completely destroyed. Several structures located nearby the blast site were also suffered major damages. Several people were injured in the blast but no one was killed. Police stated that the blast might have been caused by a leak of a 50 kg gas tube.

links.text: -gandhi, Grace (October 23, 2016). "Ledakan Pizza Hut Delivery Bekasi Diduga dari Tabung Gas". Tempo.-

Data.event_text: - Puteri Indonesia Perdamaian 2016, Ariska Putri Pertiwi was crowned Miss Grand International 2016 in the coronation night held at Las Vegas Strip, in Las Vegas, United States. She was the first ever Indonesian to win Miss Grand beauty pageant, one of the grand slam pageant in the world.

links.text: -"Miss Indonesia chooses Clinton, Miss Philippines chooses Trump, Miss Indonesia wins Miss Grand International 2016". Coconuts Media. Retrieved October 26, 2016.-
-"Indonesia brings home Miss Grand International 2016 title". The Jakarta Post. Retrieved October 27, 2016.-

-"5 interesting facts about Miss Grand International 2016 winner Ariska Pertiwi". Rappler. Retrieved October 26, 2016.-
-"Ariska Putri Pertiwi crowned Miss Grand International 2016". The Times of India. Retrieved October 26, 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Indonesian murderer Jessica Kumala Wongso was convicted guilty and was sentenced to 20 years in jail after proved to have murdered Wayan Mirna Salihin on 6 January 2016.

links.text: -"Jessica Divonis Hukuman 20 Tahun Penjara". Liputan 6. 27 October 2016. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A DHC-4 Caribou carrying construction materials with 4 crews on board went missing over Ilaga Pass while on approach to Ilaga.

links.text: -"Pesawat kargo hilang di Papua". 31 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: The wreckage of the missing DHC-4 Caribou has been found by Indonesian search and rescue team. The aircraft had impacted a hill and was pulverized by the impact. No survivors were found on the crash site.

links.text: -"Pesawat Kargo Caribou yang Hilang di Papua Ditemukan". Okezone. November 2016. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: A nail bomb exploded on a roadside in Bantul after being stepped by a buffalo. No one was injured in the incident, but the buffalo was killed in the blast.

links.text: -"Duarr! Benda Diduga Bom Meledak Terinjak Kerbau di Bantul". Detik. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Batam ferry sinking - A ferry carrying 101 passengers and crews sank off the coast of Nongsa in Batam, Riau Islands. The ferry was carrying illegal Indonesian workers from Malaysia when it sank during a thunderstorm. Survivors stated that the ferry was docking at the time when a big wave struck and capsized on its side. 39 people survived the sinking, while 44 were missing. At least 18 bodies, including a 6 month old baby, were recovered from the sea. Search and Rescue Team were immediately assembled. A crisis centre was set up in Nongsa.

links.text: -"Diduga kelebihan penumpang, kapal TKI karam, 18 meninggal". BBC News Indonesia. BBC. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-
-"Kapal tenggelam di Batam, puluhan TKI hilang". Rappler. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - At least 54 bodies were recovered during search and rescue operation of the Batam ferry sinking.

links.text: -"Musibah Kapal Tenggelam di Batam: 54 Tewas, 6 Dinyatakan Hilang". DW. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: -  protest - Thousands of hardliner Muslims joined a march in Jakarta to protest the province's ethnic Chinese and Christian Governor Basuki Tjahaja Purnama (known in Indonesia as Ahok) after his remarks on 5 October 2016 about Sura Al-Ma'ida Ayah 51 went viral on the internet. The remarks was made by him while campaigning in Pulau Pramuka, Kepulauan Seribu. The remarks sparked condemnation by hardline Muslims across Indonesia. The protest started peacefully early on the day, however it ended violently after several protesters refused to move from the protest area by the Indonesian Police. 350 people were hurt in the following clash, with 1 people died after suffering breathing problem.

links.text: -"Polda Metro: 350 Orang Terluka Akibat Demo 4 November Ricuh". Liputan 6. 8 November 2016. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-
-"Demo 4 November". Liputan 6. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - President Joko Widodo addressed the nation in response to the  protest and had asked Indonesians to stay calm.

links.text: -"Ini Pidato Presiden Jokowi Soal Demo 4 November". Tempo. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - 4 year old Intan Olivia Marbun was killed after a molotov bomb exploded in front of a church in Samarinda, East Kalimantan. The perpetrator, Muhammad Juhanda, and 3 toddlers were injured in the attack. The attack was inspired by ISIS, marking the third ISIS attack to occur in Indonesia in less than a month.

links.text: -"#RIPIntan, Lukisan Intan Olivia Korban Bom Samarinda Ini Viral di Medsos". Detik. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - At least 37 houses were damaged after a strong, magnitude 5.8 earthquake rocked the city of Malang in East Java. No one was killed in the incident.

links.text: -"Ini Penampakan Kerusakan di Malang Akibat Gempa 5,8 SR". Detik. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - 15 people went missing after their boat collided with a Vietnamese vessel in Tuban, East Java.

links.text: -"2 Kapal Tabrakan di Perairan Tuban, 15 Awak Kapal Dinyatakan Hilang". Detik. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - A Bell 412 EP helicopter carrying 5 people on board went missing over Borneo while en route to Malinau Regency in North Kalimantan. The helicopter, registered as HA-5166, had its last contact with Tarakan Tower at 11.29 local time. A search and rescue team was deployed in response to the disappearance.

links.text: -"Helikopter TNI AD Hilang Kontak di Malinau, Kalimantan Utara". Tempo. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Anti-terror squad raided a house in Majalengka in West Java and arrested a terrorist in the operation. They found that the terrorist had bought materials for making bombs. Indonesian police confirmed that the blast would be three times more powerful than the bombs that had been used in the 2002 Bali bombings, in which a car bomb exploded in Legian Street, killing 202 people. The police later revealed that the terrorist was intended to attack several vital places in Jakarta, including the People's Representatives Council building, Indonesian Police Headquarters, Foreign embassies (including the U.S consulate), T.V stations, several "undisclosed" religious sites, and cafes in Jakarta. The attack was supposed to take place on the New Year's Eve. Had the attack occurred, the total number of casualties could surpass the number of victims in the 2002 Bali bombings.

links.text: -"Tersangka Teroris di Majalengka Rakit Bom, Ini Targetnya". Tempo. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-
-"Polri: Bom Rakitan Teroris Majalengka Diledakkan Akhir Tahun". Liputan 6. 25 November 2016. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: - Indonesian anti terror squad arrested a man in Northern Aceh suspected to be involved in the Majalengka terror plot.

links.text: -"Densus 88 Tangkap Terduga Teroris Jaringan Majalengka di Aceh Utara". Detik. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: Search and rescue team found the wreckage of the helicopter that had gone missing over Borneo on . At least 1 person survived the crash with injuries, while 3 people were killed in the crash. Their bodies were later recovered by search and rescue team. The pilot of the flight was still missing.

links.text: -"Heli TNI AD Hilang Kontak di Kalimantan Ditemukan". Liputan 6. 27 November 2016. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-
-"Tiga Jenazah Korban Helikopter Jatuh Ditemukan, Pilot Masih Dicari". Kompas. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: Indonesian Minister of Education and Social Culture Muhadjir stated his intention to remove the National Examination Test programme.

links.text: -"Ini Pengganti UN Bila Dihapuskan pada 2017". Tribun News. Retrieved 27 December 2016.-

Data.event_text: A massive demonstration involving more than 200.000 hardliner Muslims was held in Jakarta. Protesters demanded for the imprisonment of Jakarta's Christian and Chinese Governor Basuki Tjahaja Purnama due to his remarks on 5 October about Sura Al-Ma'ida Ayah 51. The protest was peaceful unlike the previous on 4 November. However, reports had emerged that protesters attacked multiple journalists on the scene, which drew condemnation from the public.

links.text: -"AKSI DAMAI 2 DESEMBER". Okezone. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: The Indonesian National Police arrested 10 people suspected of "planning an assault to the government".

links.text: -"Di luar aksi 212, Polri tangkap 10 tokoh terkait 'perencanaan percobaan makar'". BBC News Indonesia. BBC. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - A PZL M28 Skytruck belonged to the Indonesian National Police lost contact with air traffic controller near Lingga, Riau Islands. The plane was approaching Batam when the incident occurred while carrying 13 police personnel. Local fishermen joined the search and rescue operation. Later, several personal belongings were retrieved from the sea near the area where the plane had lost contact.

links.text: -"Ini Nama 13 Polisi yang Ada di Pesawat Polri yang Hilang Kontak". Kompas. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-
-"Barang-barang Korban Pesawat Jatuh: Topi dan 2 Pas Foto Polisi". Detik. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - The first body part from one of the passengers of the missing Skytruck was found by search and rescue team. All passengers and crews were declared dead.

links.text: -"Potongan Jasad Korban Ditemukan dan Langsung Dibawa ke RS Bhayangkara Batam - Tribun Batam". Tribun News. 4 December 2016. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - Aceh earthquake - A shallow and violent magnitude 6.5 earthquake rocked the Aceh region on the morning of 7 , killing at least 104 people and injuring more than 1.000 people.

links.text: -"Gempa Aceh". Tribun News. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - Indonesian National Police arrested three people in a homestay in Bekasi. In a press conference, investigators stated that the terrorist were using TATP explosives. Investigators said that the bombs were highly explosive and added that the terrorists were planning to execute the bombing on the Presidential Palace on 11  during guards exchange.

links.text: -"Bom Panci di Bekasi Berdaya Ledak Tinggi, Ini Bahan Bakunya". Tempo. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - Jakarta Governor Basuki Tjahaja Purnama attended his first blasphemy trial.

links.text: -"Fakta seputar sidang perdana Ahok". Beritagar. 13 December 2016. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - An Indonesian Air Force Lockheed C-130 Hercules slammed onto Mount Lisuwa in Wamena while on approach to Wamena Airport, killing all 13 people on board.

links.text: -"Pesawat Hercules TNI AU Jatuh di Wamena". Tempo. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: Three terrorists were shot dead by the Indonesian National Police at a house in South Tangerang, West Java. Police then safely detonated the homemade bombs that they had discovered in the house. According to the police, the attackers were resisting arrests and threw bombs at the police, which forced them to shoot the terrorists on the spot. The police later added that the three terrorists were planning to attack police  by throwing bombs into a police box during the New Year's Eve, similar to the earlier attack in Jakarta in January.

links.text: -"Tiga terduga teroris di Tangsel 'melawan dengan melempar bom' sebelum ditembak". BBC News Indonesia. BBC Indonesia. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: An Indonesian phrase, called "Om Telolet Om" went viral in social media and throughout the world. The phrase, translated in English as "Uncle, Honk Your Horn, Uncle" went viral after a video showing a group of children asked for a bus driver to honk their horn in Jepara, East Java was shared on social media (although several people claimed that the phrase went viral through spamming)"Om telolet om Bus pertama yang membuat tren klakson ini mendunia". BBC News Indonesia. BBC Indonesia. Retrieved 2 .

- Indonesian Police shot dead 2 people after resisting arrests and assaulted police in Jatiluhur Dam, Purwakarta, West Java. Another 2 people were arrested. All of them were arrested due to "supporting terror attack" as they were planning to blown up the Jatiluhur Dam, according to the a paper founded by the police. Had the attack occurred, the whole Jakarta would be submerged in water and thousands could be killed in the act.

links.text: -"Mengerikan Kalau Waduk Jatiluhur sampai Diledakkan Teroris". Suara. 25 December 2016. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: 6 people were suffocated to death and 5 people were seriously injured when a group of armed robber held them as hostages inside a toilet with no ventilation. The robbery occurred in an elite neighborhood of Pulomas in East Jakarta. The victims were held for "several hours", which caused a lack of oxygen (hypoxia). A nationwide manhunt was ordered by the Chief of the National Police.

links.text: -"Perampokan Sadis Pulomas, 6 Orang Tewas di Kamar Mandi". Tempo. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: Former Head of the Indonesian National Football Association La Nyala Mataliti was convicted not guilty by prosecutor.

links.text: -"BREAKING NEWS: La Nyalla Bebas". Tempo. Retrieved 2 January 2017.-

Data.event_text: - 2 people suspected as accomplices in the robbery in Pulomas were arrested by the police.
